00:02:28,010 --> 00:02:31,660
♫ Let's work. Let's work ♫

16
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:36,400
♫ Shut up and let's work. Let's work. Let's work ♫

17
00:02:43,799 --> 00:02:48,200
Can we get started now?

18
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:50,200
Yes? Yes.

19
00:03:04,299 --> 00:03:09,000
All right! Concentration Claps! Concentration Claps!

20
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,300
You know that we have class outside next period, right?

21
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:13,999
- Yes!
- Yes!

22
00:03:13,999 --> 00:03:15,499
Clean up your desks. Let's head outside.

23
00:03:15,499 --> 00:03:18,900
And make sure you get all the supplies you need! And don't run!

24
00:03:24,399 --> 00:03:27,099
Wow, everyone is doing such a great job!

25
00:03:27,099 --> 00:03:29,600
Let me know if you need more flowers.

26
00:03:34,099 --> 00:03:38,000
Wow. You made a butterfly out of dirt, huh, Gyeong Eun?

27
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:40,700
I thought it'd be pretty even if I made it out of rocks and dirt.

28
00:03:40,700 --> 00:03:43,700
Wow, I didn't even think of doing this.

29
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:45,000
How cool!

30
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,600
I'll give you a "good job!" stamp.

31
00:04:04,099 --> 00:04:08,199
Everyone, don't go anywhere. Stay right where you are, okay?

32
00:04:08,199 --> 00:04:09,800
- Yes, Teacher.
- Yes, Teacher.

33
00:04:21,199 --> 00:04:24,300
E-Excuse me! Are you all right?

34
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:27,199
What should I do...

35
00:04:29,099 --> 00:04:30,600
Sir!

36
00:04:34,799 --> 00:04:36,600
Oh, no!

37
00:04:38,599 --> 00:04:42,500
Sir! Sir, wake up!

38
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:43,999
Sir!

39
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:49,200
Damn it!

40
00:04:51,299 --> 00:04:53,199
Um, what could it be this time?

41
00:04:53,199 --> 00:04:56,900
I wonder what company made his phone. It sure is tough.

42
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:58,700
It doesn't break no matter how many times he throws it.

43
00:04:58,700 --> 00:05:03,000
And chairs too. The stuff in our hotel is really sturdy.

44
00:05:10,799 --> 00:05:12,500
Don't we have a meeting with Mr. Kingston at 4 p.m.?

45
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:15,299
Um, yes, sir. We're all ready.

46
00:05:15,299 --> 00:05:17,100
All we need there now is for you to go.

47
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:31,699
Even though we have the finest business-class room,

48
00:05:31,699 --> 00:05:33,399
we're holding our agreement meeting at another hotel?

49
00:05:33,399 --> 00:05:35,000
Should I consider this a challenge?

50
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,199
Or should I blame this on the incompetency of the staff?

51
00:05:40,299 --> 00:05:43,900
Well, that is, um...

52
00:05:43,900 --> 00:05:50,599
Because that hotel is part of their chain... we just let them have their way...

53
00:05:50,599 --> 00:05:52,800
The next agreement meeting in New York must be at our hotel no matter what.

54
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,799
- Um, of course, sir.
- Of course, sir!

55
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:07,800
(speaking Chinese) Hello, Esteemed Guest. Can I help you?

56
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:08,700
Yes.

57
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:10,399
What are you looking for?

58
00:06:10,399 --> 00:06:12,900
The staff over there at the desk can assist you with check-in.

59
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:14,599
He's so two-faced.

60
00:06:14,599 --> 00:06:16,300
He's so pretentious...

61
00:06:16,300 --> 00:06:17,499
Thank you.

62
00:06:45,299 --> 00:06:48,699
He seems to be homeless. Is it really okay if we take him in?

63
00:06:48,699 --> 00:06:51,800
Let's just wait and see. If anything, we can send him elsewhere.

64
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:54,500
They said he doesn't have a guardian* though.
*—next of kin or other person who can authorize treatment

65
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:55,800
Excuse me!

66
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,100
Yes?

67
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:02,400
I'm... that man's guardian.

68
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:04,599
Oh, I see.

69
00:07:04,599 --> 00:07:06,499
- Nice job.
- Thank you.

70
00:07:07,499 --> 00:07:11,600
Mr. Kingston. How about having a meal at our hotel before you leave?

71
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:14,499
Well, my schedule is too tight.

72
00:07:14,499 --> 00:07:17,300
Too tight, huh? That's a shame.

73
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:23,600
But we just hired our main chef from Belgium who specializes in Mexican food.

74
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:26,500
- Ugh, look at his grudge...
- It makes me sick.

75
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:31,400
Oh, I'll rearrange my schedule then.

76
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:34,600
Okay. Then I'll give you a call later.

77
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,000
Okay.

78
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:49,500
What, um, brings Mr. Kingston all the way to our hotel?

79
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:51,500
He's been resisting until now.

80
00:07:52,699 --> 00:07:56,300
Mr. Kingston's favorite food is Mexican cuisine.

81
00:07:56,300 --> 00:07:58,899
And his parents are Belgian.

82
00:08:05,999 --> 00:08:07,500
Yeah, Mom?

83
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:11,800
Just what kind of herbalist is he this time?

84
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:16,399
Does he specialize in back issues? Or herbal acupuncture?

85
00:08:16,399 --> 00:08:19,299
Oh, so he's kind of good-looking, huh?

86
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:24,999
Two p.m. on Saturday? At the SH Arpensia Hotel?

87
00:08:24,999 --> 00:08:28,000
The steak there is good.

88
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:33,100
All right, already! I'll do my best.

89
00:08:33,100 --> 00:08:35,699
All right. Bye, now.

90
00:08:37,099 --> 00:08:39,499
Doesn't she ever get tired of doing this?

91
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:43,600
Oh, well. I'll go to a fancy place and get a free meal out of it, at least.

92
00:08:48,599 --> 00:08:49,900
Oh, yeah!

93
00:08:57,638 --> 00:09:00,000
[Comments about the "I Love Ji Su Fan Meeting"]

94
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:05,899
[droolingonjisu: Are you going to Ji Su's "Music Gayo" live performance?]

95
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:10,100
[ifonlyiwereyounger: Of course! How could I miss that?]

96
00:09:10,100 --> 00:09:11,800
[jisuswife: I felt like I was going to die because I missed the fan meeting

97
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:13,300
but it's even more unbearable now that I've seen everyone's comments about it!]

98
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:17,699
Wait. Should I correct their spellings or just let it be?

99
00:09:19,399 --> 00:09:24,199
No. If I become too prim here, they'll hate me.

100
00:09:24,199 --> 00:09:26,599
It won't help my Ji Su at all.

101
00:09:26,599 --> 00:09:29,200
I have to finish all that, too!

102
00:09:41,899 --> 00:09:44,100
I wonder if he's okay.

103
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:45,699
You can't leave the hospital now!

104
00:09:45,699 --> 00:09:50,000
I'm fine. Why do I waste money by lying down here?

105
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:52,599
But still, it'd be good if you stayed in the hospital today.

106
00:09:52,599 --> 00:09:54,200
No, no, no.

107
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:58,600
Before this... my hospital fees cost a lot, right?

108
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:01,199
It really wasn't much. You don't need to worry.

109
00:10:01,199 --> 00:10:04,000
One infusion barely costs anything.

110
00:10:07,699 --> 00:10:09,100
Here.

111
00:10:10,499 --> 00:10:14,900
This was going to be my wife's, but I want you to have it instead.

112
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:17,399
Why are you giving me something that's meant for your wife?

113
00:10:17,399 --> 00:10:19,200
Your wife will scold you for sure, sir!

114
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:23,100
No, no! You saved my life!

115
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:25,000
Please accept this as a token of my appreciation.

116
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:30,300
Then I won't decline your offer and I'll enjoy this.

117
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:32,799
I actually really like apples.

118
00:10:34,799 --> 00:10:37,000
Thank you.

119
00:10:49,099 --> 00:10:51,800
My purse, my cellphone, my keys, and my wallet.

120
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:55,800
Wallet... wallet, keys.

121
00:10:56,599 --> 00:10:58,000
Oh, no, I'm late!

122
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:09,500
Perfect.

123
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:25,000
My cellphone!

124
00:11:34,099 --> 00:11:37,800
Wait! No! Please wait!

125
00:11:48,100 --> 00:11:51,600
What's wrong with you all? This is a crucial time!

126
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:54,199
This is perfect for us to be falsely accused of insider trading!

127
00:11:57,699 --> 00:11:59,599
Um, CEO.

128
00:11:59,599 --> 00:12:03,699
This was what Chairman directly ordered us to do via the Red Call—

129
00:12:03,699 --> 00:12:05,600
The Chairman?

130
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,900
Director Gang.

131
00:12:06,900 --> 00:12:10,399
Are you working here without even knowing who the owner is here?

132
00:12:10,399 --> 00:12:12,500
Do you not even know who you belong to?

133
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:14,399
It's been ages since the hotel split from them!

134
00:12:14,399 --> 00:12:16,900
Do you still think that you're the Chief Secretary at Seong Hyeon Group?

135
00:12:22,699 --> 00:12:25,199
I should just destroy that thing first.

136
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:30,400
Yes, Attorney Park?

137
00:12:32,699 --> 00:12:35,200
This is a Red Call that's connected to the head office at SH Group.

138
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:37,799
How dare he use a Red Call to call us when he's a mere attorney?

139
00:12:37,799 --> 00:12:41,000
He's the Group attorney and one of the chairman's closest confidantes.

140
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,699
It'd be best... for you to, um... pick up, sir.

141
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:45,800
It's Lee Jae In.

142
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,900
I'm sure that an attorney for Seong Hyeon Group has no business with our hotel.

143
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:54,099
I'll head there, then. Let's talk in person.

144
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:58,900
I'll be gone for just two hours.

145
00:12:58,900 --> 00:13:00,999
Take care of the issue regarding the new hotel to be built in Hawaii

146
00:13:00,999 --> 00:13:03,699
and the opening ceremony at our hotel on Jeju Island.

147
00:13:03,699 --> 00:13:05,400
We'll start our meeting as soon as I get back.

148
00:13:13,899 --> 00:13:15,999
He might as well just tell us not to breathe!

149
00:13:15,999 --> 00:13:17,800
That asshole.

150
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:34,000
Geez. I'll never live out my given life span.

151
00:13:37,099 --> 00:13:40,199
He said we would have two hours. Let's hurry it up.

152
00:14:23,099 --> 00:14:25,599
Are you all right? You're not hurt, are you?

153
00:14:25,599 --> 00:14:28,599
I'm fine. I should've looked where I was going. I'm sorry.

154
00:14:33,599 --> 00:14:35,800
Yeah, Mom.

155
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:38,099
Yeah, I told you. I'm here.

156
00:14:38,099 --> 00:14:40,099
All right already! I'll do well.

157
00:14:40,099 --> 00:14:41,400
Okay.

158
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,800
Can I help you find your way?

159
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:47,399
Our coffee shop is that way.

160
00:14:47,399 --> 00:14:50,100
- Um, what about the rest room?
- The rest room?

161
00:14:50,100 --> 00:14:52,100
If you turn left at the corner, it'll be right there.

162
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:54,099
And the coffee shop is this way.

163
00:14:54,099 --> 00:14:55,599
Oh, thank you.

164
00:14:58,500 --> 00:14:59,999
She's clearly here for a marriage meeting.

165
00:14:59,999 --> 00:15:02,099
Wow, their staff is really well trained!

166
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,800
You're here, CEO Lee?

167
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:16,099
Piss off.

168
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:24,599
I'm not your friend right now. I'm Seong Hyeon Group legal consultant.

169
00:15:24,599 --> 00:15:27,100
What's this about that you even used a Red Call to contact me?

170
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:30,199
"How dare he use a Red Call to call us when he's a mere attorney?"

171
00:15:30,199 --> 00:15:32,099
Exactly.

172
00:15:32,099 --> 00:15:35,699
How dare some lawyer tell me, the CEO, to come and go as he pleases?

173
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:44,500
The Chairman changed his will.

174
00:15:54,338 --> 00:15:56,099
[Testator: Lee Gyu Cheol
Witness: Park Hyeong Jun
Witness: Gang Min Ju]

175
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:06,900
Lee Jae In.

176
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:11,099
This isn't a joke.

177
00:16:11,099 --> 00:16:13,099
I'm not joking around, either.

178
00:16:13,099 --> 00:16:16,500
This is Grandpa's fortune, so he should be free to do with it as he wants.

179
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:18,699
It's none of my business to butt in.

180
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:23,000
Fine. But first, take a seat.

181
00:16:31,199 --> 00:16:33,600
Don't you understand what this means?

182
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:36,400
If you get the Chairman's shares on top of the ones you already have,

183
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:39,900
you can completely take over Seong Hyeon Group!

184
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:42,000
But in exchange, I have to marry the woman he wants me to marry.

185
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:43,729
That's the condition!

186
00:16:43,729 --> 00:16:47,600
I have no intention of doing that.

187
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:49,600
Aren't you curious about who that woman is, at the very least?

188
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:50,800
Not in the slightest.

189
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:53,099
Because I know who it is, even without being told.

190
00:16:53,099 --> 00:16:55,199
This isn't the first time this has happened.

191
00:16:55,199 --> 00:16:58,799
Even when he wrote his first will three years ago...

192
00:16:58,799 --> 00:17:01,000
It's not Han Ju Hee.

193
00:17:04,899 --> 00:17:08,700
Well, regardless of who it is, I have no interest in any of this.

194
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:10,899
This has nothing to do with me,

195
00:17:10,899 --> 00:17:12,300
even if he said he'd hand over his entire fortune.

196
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:13,900
I'm perfectly satisfied with what I have now.

197
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:16,000
I can get back on my feet under my own power.

198
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:22,399
If Grandpa did this by himself, then so can I.

199
00:17:22,399 --> 00:17:25,200
This woman is someone that neither of us knows.

200
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:27,699
And I'm sure that other people don't know who she is, either.

201
00:17:27,699 --> 00:17:32,200
You may not want the fortune, but that may not be the case with this woman!

202
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:34,000
So what?

203
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:38,499
When I said that this has nothing to do with me, I meant it.

204
00:17:41,799 --> 00:17:47,200
I thought you made the right decision last time, too.

205
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:49,199
But not this time.

206
00:17:51,099 --> 00:17:52,899
I don't think this is the right choice.

207
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:06,800
[Last Will and Testament]

208
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,900
[Legatee: Kim Da Hyeon
Relation: Savior]

209
00:18:08,900 --> 00:18:10,200
[Legatee: Lee Jae In
Relation: Eldest Grandson]

210
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:17,700
The chairman doesn't care which guy she marries.
[This will be executed on the following conditions:
1) When Kim Da Hyeon and Lee Jae In marry one another.]

211
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:19,600
Even if it's Tae Ha.

212
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:24,000
That means whoever marries that woman first will become the next owner of Seong Hyeon Group!

213
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:28,699
You know very well how much Tae Ha wants Seong Hyeon Group!

214
00:18:29,899 --> 00:18:31,900
Damn it all.

215
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:43,399
Let's do it, then, Grandpa.

216
00:18:44,900 --> 00:18:47,500
I don't enjoy losing games either.

217
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:06,700
Here, let me give you a stamp.

218
00:19:07,700 --> 00:19:11,300
Ms. Kim, I have five "good job" stamps now.

219
00:19:11,300 --> 00:19:12,599
Oh, really?

220
00:19:12,599 --> 00:19:16,200
What about me, Teacher? Why aren't you giving me a stamp?

221
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:18,299
Let's see here.

222
00:19:18,299 --> 00:19:20,800
Here you go. All right!

223
00:19:21,700 --> 00:19:23,699
Great job!

224
00:19:23,699 --> 00:19:28,899
I'll give stamps to those who do their best during Phys Ed, so do your best!

225
00:19:28,899 --> 00:19:31,400
- Yes, Ms. Kim!
- Yes, Ms. Kim!

226
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:38,199
I wonder what kind of woman she is that the Chairman loves her so much?

227
00:19:38,199 --> 00:19:40,700
Probably a nine-tailed fox.
(Korean legend: fox that assumes woman's form to prey on men)

228
00:19:40,700 --> 00:19:43,299
There's no other rational explanation as to how this could've happened.

229
00:19:43,299 --> 00:19:47,300
Hey, who knows? She might be beautiful, just like Yang Guifei*.
(*- one of the "Four Beauties" of ancient China)

230
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:52,800
And thanks to her, that entire country fell to ruin. Because of a woman.

231
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:55,200
Geez.

232
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:03,599
Come over here! Over here!

233
00:20:05,899 --> 00:20:07,900
This way!

234
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:44,000
All right! Gather around!

235
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:47,799
Back into the classroom now, everyone. That's all for Phys Ed today!

236
00:20:47,799 --> 00:20:49,099
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

237
00:20:49,099 --> 00:20:51,800
All right, good work!

238
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:54,100
Oh, it's so hot.

239
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:56,800
Ms. Kim Da Hyeon, please come to the teachers' office.

240
00:21:18,599 --> 00:21:20,200
Hello.

241
00:21:22,299 --> 00:21:24,599
Um, what brings you here?

242
00:21:28,300 --> 00:21:29,899
Please take a seat.

243
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:52,000
Um, have you heard of a man named Lee Gyu Cheol?

244
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:56,200
Lee Gyu Cheol... Lee Gyu Cheol?

245
00:21:56,200 --> 00:21:59,199
I don't have a child by that name in my class.

246
00:21:59,199 --> 00:22:01,700
They must be in a different class.

247
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:08,899
